Mavericks rally to beat Heat 95-93
2011-06-03 06:02:24 GMT
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Dallas Mavericks shrugged off a 15-point deficit in the fourth quarter, coming back to beat Miami Heat 95-93 in Game 2 of 2011 NBA finals on Friday.Although with a torn tendon on his middle finger of the left hand, German all-star Dirk Nowitzki led surge-back and swept all the final nine points for Dallas.The two sides tied 1-1 in the best-of-seven final series. 
